cs.AR, cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.DC 

This paper deals with memory consistency models, which are a fundamental aspect of computer architecture and programming languages. The paper discusses axiomatic and operational definitions of memory models, which are topics that fall under the categories of programming languages (cs.PL), logic (cs.LO), software engineering (cs.SE), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach to defining memory models, which could be of interest to researchers in the area of computer architecture (cs.AR).
